The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Athletics academy in Steel City
 FROM OUR CORRESPONDENT Jamshedpur: After football and archery, the Steel City has given birth to an athletics academy (Tata Athletics Academy) for the middle and long distance runners. Here, on Sunday, Tata Steel managing director B. Muthuraman inaugurated the academy in the presence of Flying Sikh Milkha Singh. Singh will be visiting the academy once or twice ayear to give his advice for the budding athletes. Nicolai from Belarus has been appointed the chief coach. Nicolai will be assisted by two Indians  Bagicha Singh and Satnam Singh. The programme was attended by former Olympian K. L. Powel, Edward Sequera, Charles Borromeo, AAFI secretary Lalit Bhanot and others.  Copyright 
